OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1784915311
OL,3,CPressure mounts on Welsh Government
OL,4,Cafter figures show rise in NHS waiting
OL,5,Ctimes
OL,7,F"We're doing things differently to
OL,8,Fprevious approaches. Through our
OL,9,Fclinically-led surgical hub programme
OL,10,Fwe will strengthen local capacity, get
OL,11,Fpatients treated quicker and ensure
OL,12,Fthat elective care demand is managed
OL,13,Fmore sustainably within day-to-day NHS
OL,14,Factivity. We are committed to
OL,15,Fdelivering our investment to support
OL,16,Fwaiting list reductions this year."
OL,18,FReform Wales' Shadow Health Minister
OL,19,FJames Evans insisted Plaid Cymru
OL,20,F"cannot distance itself from the state
OL,21,Fof our NHS".
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@cO]|D@AOU}D@KO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/9
