OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1784915311
OL,3,CPressure mounts on Welsh Government
OL,4,Cafter figures show rise in NHS waiting
OL,5,Ctimes
OL,7,FHis Welsh Conservative counterpart
OL,8,FNatasha Ashgar added: "Plaid Cymru
OL,9,Fcannot escape responsibility for this.
OL,10,FThey propped up the previous Welsh
OL,11,FLabour Government by supporting its
OL,12,Fbudgets and are now running the health
OL,13,Fservice. Patients need urgent action,
OL,14,Fnot more empty promises."
OL,16,FMr ap Gwynfor thanked NHS staff for
OL,17,Ftheir "dedication and compassion" and
OL,18,Fpartly blamed hot weather for record
OL,19,FA&E attendances.
OL,26,@pD@WOUvD@YO]yD@GOUyD@aO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/9
